<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Georgia_TKR on 05-03-2001 10:59 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]
This is not fair to those of us who are guildless! What if I have no friends in EQ? What if everyone hates me? I'll never get past Step 3.
[/QUOTE]

If everyone hates you; if you aren't in a guild; if you don't have any friends whatsoever, you shouldn't be playing this game. It's a socially-focused game.

 [QUOTE]
Do you feel for the clerics who will never have the chance to complete Step 3? I don't.
[/QUOTE]

Yes, I do. There is one cleric who has been nagging guilds to get help with this part for a very long time. You can do multiple Ixiblat Fers. Her problem isn't the way she asks... it's her reputation for being a moronic cleric who cares for nothing but herself. She won't heal anyone in a group unless someone asks her and she melees and nukes. That's her problem. Not mine. Do I feel for her? Yes, because she honestly tries to get her epic.

 [QUOTE]
Your complaints revolve around the supposed fact that you must be in an uberguild to complete the quest. (Then you say your guild has 2 cleric epics, but it's not an uberguild. /boggle )
[/QUOTE]

Actually, I said you DO NOT have to be in an uberguild to finish the quest. I just politely pointed out that most guilds that get Ragefire are uberguilds because they feel they can walk all over the smaller guilds that are trying very hard to mobilize to kill. My guild isn't uber because it has two cleric epics. We had Ragefire KSed by uber guilds TWICE... and we almost lost the last one due to the fact that our cleric went LD and Ragefire rotted prematurely (kind of the GM to restore the heart, but no other items dropped). 

Uber guilds twink their clerics to the max with wonderful items galore. Uber guilds will crush people who are in smaller guilds and haven't cleared Veeshan's Peak. Uber guilds will race from spawn to spawn on patch days just because they can. Uber guilds have every one of their clerics holding epics... and I mean all of them. My guild is just dedicated towards these two clerics who have their epics and we worked damn hard to get them.

 [QUOTE]
How are the complaints I've outlined above less valid than yours?
[/QUOTE]

Because your complaints are always lined with some undertone knee-to-groin attitude towards nonPVP servers.

 [QUOTE]
Do you believe that if a cleric has no friends in EQ, that he/she does not deserve the epic weapon?
[/QUOTE]

No. Everyone deserves the epic if he/she is willing enough to put in the time, effort, and devotion worthy of holding such a weapon.

------------------
Georgia Gaelicmyst
Cleric of Tunare
Everlore Staff Member
http://www.everlore.com/</TEXTAREA>
